            "answer_text": "You can probably use them interchangeably. But, if I was to distinguish, it would be as follows: Educational Philosophy is probably a teaching philosophy. It is an outlook on and approach to instruction. It has to do with how a teacher approaches working with students individually and as a group. This concerns matters of instruction, evaluation, classroom magament, discipline, communication, et\u2026 Philosophy of Education is a concept about the use, purpose, and goals of education in general. This is really about how guidelines are created for districts, states, and nations etc\u2026 This concerns matters of educational standards, tracking, goals, expectations, financing, etc\u2026 ",
